        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 11 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lodge Grass, or 29 miles south of Hardin, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 45 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lodge Grass, Busby, Crow Agency, Kirby, and I-90 from Lodge Grass
to near Hardin.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
